Dear Recipient,
&nbsp;
Thank you for confirming the validity of your email address and also accepting my grant donation fund. My charitable foundation (The Warren Buffett Charitable Foundation) technically is responsible for awarding grant donations, but I have always wanted to make a personal donation to random individuals in any part of the world and that is why I have decided to give 805,000.00 United States Dollars ] to you. It gives me great joy to finally be able to make this donation to you, let's make the world a better place by giving and solving each other's problems, all people have the right to opportunity, equity and dignity.
&nbsp;
Visit the web page and read and listen to my interview -
https://www.reuters.com/markets/us/warren-buffetts-charitable-giving-tops-51-billion-2023-06-22/
&nbsp;
I am hoping that you will be able to use the money wisely and judiciously, please
you have to do your part to also alleviate the level of poverty in your region, help as many you can help once you have this money in your personal account because that is the only objective of donating this money to you in the first place. It is categorically clear that you have emerged as our beneficiary. I want to inform you about my plan to send your grant fund to you via my payout bank.
&nbsp;
Kindly confirm readiness by formally introducing yourself in detail.
&nbsp;
Full Name:&nbsp;
Your Country:&nbsp;
Address: Age:&nbsp;
Occupation:&nbsp;
Cell Number:&nbsp;
Marital Status:&nbsp;
Gender:
&nbsp;
Thereafter, Authorization will be given to the attorney and to the finance firm regarding this Donation.. Please my Friend, this is my personal wealth and it doesn't need many formal procedures, and for the sake that it might seem too easy for you to receive this gift, I would crave your indulgence not to come back after these donations so that i can be able to reach other needy. I am doing this as a free-spirit gift and I made the contact myself to everyone who can see my email.
&nbsp;
I will wait for your email to do further.
&nbsp;
Best Regards
Mr. Warren Edward Buffett
Chairman and CEO of Berkshire

